{"id":57,"question":"Can you point me to where in the material this teaching on death is discussed?","rag_answer":"Based on the documents, the teaching on death appears in several places:\n\nThe discussion begins with an explicit intention: \"I want to go into death. I want to talk about death. I think death is interesting to bring at this point.\"\n\nThe teaching connects death to specific numbers in what appears to be a framework or map. Number 5 is identified as death, with death occurring again at number 10, and again at number 12, while number 3 is associated with life.\n\nThe material elaborates: \"every time it goes up you live and then number one, five, ten, twelve you die... Number five is psychedelic, it is psychedelic, it's also a near-death experience for many.\"\n\nThe facilitator notes: \"I cannot count at all how many deaths I've seen. It's a percentage in the room all the time. In any room, there's a death that will happen, in a training or in a workshop.\"\n\nThe teaching also touches on the **psychology of death and acceptance**: Those who are okay with dying are the ones who don't, while those who don't want to die are the ones who do — and those who are accepting of death are the ones who recover.\n\nFinally, there is a philosophical dimension: intuitively, \"no one dies\" — everyone really just transforms into another state.","label":"Framework is clearly the \"12 Stages\", LLM needs to be able to synthesize this"}
